# Frontend UI Standards

## Mobile-First Requirement
- **All layouts start from mobile** (`base` styles = mobile) then scale up with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`
- Touch targets minimum **44×44px** (`min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px]`)
- Tap-friendly spacing: minimum `p-3` on interactive elements

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — mobile-first responsive
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">

// ❌ WRONG — desktop-first (using max-* to downscale)
<div className="grid grid-cols-3 max-sm:grid-cols-1">
```

## Component Rules
- **Always** use Shadcn UI primitives (`Button`, `Card`, `Dialog`, `Sheet`, etc.) — do not build from scratch
- Extend Shadcn with `cn()` (from `@/lib/utils`) — never override with inline styles
- Loading states: use Shadcn `Skeleton` — no spinners unless inside a `Button`
- Error states: use `Alert` variant `destructive`

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
<Button variant="destructive" size="lg" className="w-full sm:w-auto">Cancel Booking</Button>
```

## Next.js App Router Patterns
- Server Components by default — add `'use client'` only when necessary (event handlers, hooks, browser APIs)
- Data fetching in Server Components via `async/await` — NOT in `useEffect`
- Route handlers in `app/api/` must validate input with shared Zod schemas from `packages/shared`
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` per route segment

## Typography & Colour
- Use the design token CSS variables (`--primary`, `--muted`, `--destructive`, etc.) — never hardcode hex/rgb
- Body text minimum `text-sm` (14px); never below `text-xs` for readable content

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must have accessible labels (`aria-label` or visible text)
- `Dialog` and `Sheet` components must trap focus correctly (Shadcn handles this by default)
- Colour contrast must meet WCAG AA
